<paragraph blockId="15.[148,977,373,500]" pageId="15" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[172,341,399,420]" pageId="15" pageNumber="428">Natural History.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[390,466,400,421]" pageId="15" pageNumber="428">allotype</typeStatus>
was collected in lowland rainforest among dead leafs of a broken palm, 
<taxonomicName box="[322,519,426,447]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Oenocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="15" pageNumber="428" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mapora">
<emphasis box="[322,519,426,447]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="428">Oenocarpus mapora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, that was brought up from the ground and hung in the canopy to attract beetles. The 
<typeStatus box="[491,574,453,474]" pageId="15" pageNumber="428">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected in a malaise trap in lowland rain forest.
</paragraph>
